It's a natural result of kettlebells attracting older guys and "busy dads" looking for a quick way to train with the best bang for your buck to keep in shape. If it was bodybuilding there would be constant videos shitting on him and calling him retarded but they just respect him.

You know the kettlebell community is "wholesome" because they universally love Pavel Tsatsouline even though they recognize his stuff isn't the be-all and end-all of kettlebell training, meanwhile in regular bodybuilding people always shit on and denigrate the most popular guy.

Me and my buddy have a new game where every time we pass by some small park or random green space with flowers, stones, bushes, etc. between residential buildings we argue and try to categorize it as an "English garden" or a "French garden" depending on its spatial arrangement...

Like a random empty yard with grass that some old person from the neighborhood planted a few flowers seeds on out of boredom, but it was still arranged consciously. Like William Guppy said every person has a perfect philosophy even if he or she lacks the vocabulary to express it.
